      "updated": 1714176419895,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "text": "1 hexadecimal digit represents 4 bits\nSo in Java, an integer is:\n32 bits == 8 hex digits long\nex: 0xFFFFFFFF\n\nThe MSB bit is used for signing.\n\n3 different types of packets\nTherefore 3 different implementations.\n\nAlgorithm A\nAlgorithm B\nAlgorithm C\n\n\n\nParser (Worker)\n----------------\n\nListens to Generator thread to grab packets as they come in\nCreates packets\nReads key, initializes packet key\nReads length, initializes packet length\n\nGets values based on the packet key\n\nswitch(key)\n    case KEY_1:\n        AlgorithmA.parse(packet)\n    case KEY_2:\n        AlgorithmB.parse(packet)\n    ...\n\nPlaces initialized packets on display queue\n\n\nPacket\n----------------\n\nkey: UNIQUE 2 byte integer\nlength: 2-byte integer denoting the length of <values> in bytes\nvalues: byte array",
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "1 hexadecimal digit represents 4 bits\nSo in Java, an integer is:\n32 bits == 8 hex digits long\nex: 0xFFFFFFFF\n\nThe MSB bit is used for signing.\n\n3 different types of packets\nTherefore 3 different implementations.\n\nAlgorithm A\nAlgorithm B\nAlgorithm C\n\n\n\nParser (Worker)\n----------------\n\nListens to Generator thread to grab packets as they come in\nCreates packets\nReads key, initializes packet key\nReads length, initializes packet length\n\nGets values based on the packet key\n\nswitch(key)\n    case KEY_1:\n        AlgorithmA.parse(packet)\n    case KEY_2:\n        AlgorithmB.parse(packet)\n    ...\n\nPlaces initialized packets on display queue\n\n\nPacket\n----------------\n\nkey: UNIQUE 2 byte integer\nlength: 2-byte integer denoting the length of <values> in bytes\nvalues: byte array",
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "version": 137,
      "versionNonce": 1838857967,
      "index": "a2",
      "isDeleted": false,
      "id": "DS8s0emwnxMfr0QwuZo2F",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "x": 2011.25,
      "y": 388.75,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "width": 348.6458435058594,
      "height": 100,
      "seed": 651364889,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1714176419895,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "text": "Displayer (Worker)\n----------------------\nGets packets from the queue and \ndisplays them accordingly.",
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Displayer (Worker)\n----------------------\nGets packets from the queue and \ndisplays them accordingly.",
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "version": 810,
      "versionNonce": 1121401281,
      "index": "a3",
      "isDeleted": false,
      "id": "onDbc9yCN5EtpdY3pei0I",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "x": 525.25,
      "y": 465.75,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "width": 479.2291564941406,
      "height": 1150,
      "seed": 627145687,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1714177679706,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "text": "\n\n\n\n\n\n\nWe can test this system by giving it a different\npacket one at a time and making sure that it \nproduces the correct result.\n\nOnce we do this, we can worry about the \ngeneration part.\n\nCreate test packets using byte arrays in Java.\n\n2-byte integer (unsigned)\n1001 1101 1100 0000\n\nEXAMPLE PACKET:\n\nStart of packet:  0x2B00\n                    0010 1011 0000 0000\n\nPacket Counter:   0x0000\n                    0000 0000 0000 0000\n\nKey: 0x0100\n                    0000 0001 0000 0000\n\nLength of packet: 16 -> 0x0010\n                    0000 0000 0001 0000\n\nPayload: 16 bytes (null terminated String)\n\n                    'abcdefghijklmnop\\0'\n\n                    15 characters + \\0\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n ",
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "\n\n\n\n\n\n\nWe can test this system by giving it a different\npacket one at a time and making sure that it \nproduces the correct result.\n\nOnce we do this, we can worry about the \ngeneration part.\n\nCreate test packets using byte arrays in Java.\n\n2-byte integer (unsigned)\n1001 1101 1100 0000\n\nEXAMPLE PACKET:\n\nStart of packet:  0x2B00\n                    0010 1011 0000 0000\n\nPacket Counter:   0x0000\n                    0000 0000 0000 0000\n\nKey: 0x0100\n                    0000 0001 0000 0000\n\nLength of packet: 16 -> 0x0010\n                    0000 0000 0001 0000\n\nPayload: 16 bytes (null terminated String)\n\n                    'abcdefghijklmnop\\0'\n\n                    15 characters + \\0\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n ",
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
